### Configure Supervisor Agent and LangGraph Workflow with Task Delegation (Python)

Source: https://github.com/langchain-ai/langgraph/blob/main/docs/docs/tutorials/multi_agent/agent_supervisor.md

This Python code defines a supervisor agent that utilizes the explicit task delegation tools to assign work to specialized research and math agents. It then constructs a LangGraph `StateGraph`, setting up the nodes and edges to orchestrate the flow, allowing the supervisor to direct tasks based on the generated descriptions.

```python
supervisor_agent_with_description = create_react_agent(
    model="openai:gpt-4.1",
    tools=[
        assign_to_research_agent_with_description,
        assign_to_math_agent_with_description,
    ],
    prompt=(
        "You are a supervisor managing two agents:\n"
        "- a research agent. Assign research-related tasks to this assistant\n"
        "- a math agent. Assign math-related tasks to this assistant\n"
        "Assign work to one agent at a time, do not call agents in parallel.\n"
        "Do not do any work yourself."
    ),
    name="supervisor",
)

supervisor_with_description = (
    StateGraph(MessagesState)
    .add_node(
        supervisor_agent_with_description, destinations=("research_agent", "math_agent")
    )
    .add_node(research_agent)
    .add_node(math_agent)
    .add_edge(START, "supervisor")
    .add_edge("research_agent", "supervisor")
    .add_edge("math_agent", "supervisor")
    .compile()
)
```

