### Implement Supervisor Multi-Agent System with LangGraph (Python & JS)

Source: https://github.com/langchain-ai/langgraph/blob/main/docs/docs/agents/multi-agent.md

This snippet demonstrates how to set up a supervisor-based multi-agent system using the `langgraph-supervisor` library. It defines individual agents with specific tools and prompts, and then coordinates them with a central supervisor agent to handle complex requests requiring multiple specializations. The system requires an OpenAI model for the LLM agents.

```bash
pip install langgraph-supervisor
```

```python
from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI
from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent
from langgraph_supervisor import create_supervisor

def book_hotel(hotel_name: str):
    """Book a hotel"""
    return f"Successfully booked a stay at {hotel_name}."

def book_flight(from_airport: str, to_airport: str):
    """Book a flight"""
    return f"Successfully booked a flight from {from_airport} to {to_airport}."

flight_assistant = create_react_agent(
    model="openai:gpt-4o",
    tools=[book_flight],
    prompt="You are a flight booking assistant",
    name="flight_assistant"
)

hotel_assistant = create_react_agent(
    model="openai:gpt-4o",
    tools=[book_hotel],
    prompt="You are a hotel booking assistant",
    name="hotel_assistant"
)

supervisor = create_supervisor(
    agents=[flight_assistant, hotel_assistant],
    model=ChatOpenAI(model="gpt-4o"),
    prompt=(
        "You manage a hotel booking assistant and a"
        "flight booking assistant. Assign work to them."
    )
).compile()

for chunk in supervisor.stream(
    {
        "messages": [
            {
                "role": "user",
                "content": "book a flight from BOS to JFK and a stay at McKittrick Hotel"
            }
        ]
    }
):
    print(chunk)
    print("\n")
```

